values: I was accepted at UCI!!!!! Now I just have two more to wait for...
For me, in case I need it when I'm not at home.Livy Book 21
Heard back from USC already... They didn't want me :(   Now I'm worried about the others.
YAY for having all of my applications done!!!!
It's only the first day of the quarter and my head is already spinning.
One application done... three more to go...

I wish I knew why I feel so depressed recently.  I feel so drained and I'm not sleeping well and everything irritates me.  I've felt this way for so long that I don't remember a time when I didn't feel like this.  I've cried or felt like crying almost everyday this week.  I even cried at work yesterday.  My boss was worried about me because I'd missed two days of work, which is really unusual for me, so she asked me how I was doing.  And I started to cry.  She was very understanding and told me I could take time off if I wanted just to have a break.  I felt a little better after that because I was worried she was upset with me for missing work.  And poor Brandon... I don't know how he's been able to stand me... I can barely stand myself.  Well, I think that's enough whining for now.
My econ class is over!!!! yay!!!!!  Now I just have to write my paper for history...

My dad took me to a movie and then pizza today.  We saw T3... it was actually a lot better than I thought it was going to be.  He also got me a neat little carved wood stool that he bought in the Philippines.  I don't see my dad often and I don't really like spending time with him when he is around because all he does is bitch about everything... but today he was almost nice and I actually enjoyed seeing him.   I also FINALLY got a screen for my window... yay!!!!! ... now I can get a breeze going through my room without worrying about being attacked by the wasps that live outside my window.

Happy Birthday to me!  I had a pretty good day overall.  I went to lunch with my mom (yummy, yummy thai food).  Brandon gave me a beautiful, sparkly necklace.  And I love it.  I did have to take an evil history test though.  I think the teacher was flirting with me during the test... kinda scary.  Anyways... and yes I do love the necklace in case you missed it the first time... or the second... third... =P
I can't tell anymore if it's just being tired or ... whatever... stupid stuff makes me feel like crying or sometimes I just don't care about anything anymore.  I just don't feel like me recently.

I took my history test today.  It wasn't too bad overall.  I think I did well on everything but the essay.  It was really stupid.  Oh well.  At least I can drop this test if I did really bad.  Now I get to study for my microeconomics test, which is tomorrow... yay.

Spent the day with Brandon... yay!!!  Tree hamsters are the best!  Bryan finally got Chobits back so i can borrow it now... but evil friend left the last three episodes in his computer at school... he promised i'd get them by next week though...  I don't think I'll get to watch much anyways since I have two tests this week and I'm already behind on my reading :(

Well, I've finally started one of these.  Brandon is pleased.  He has been bugging me forever to get one.  This is going to be a really short post because I don't have anything else to say. Maybe I'll think of something later...
